## Abstract

Keyvoy is open-source embedded wallet infrastructure for Canton — giving developers production-ready TypeScript SDKs to add authentication, wallet provisioning, and transaction signing to their Canton apps in minutes. It also provides AI agents (Claude, GPT, LangChain) with secure, policy-gated Canton access through MCP tools and native SDKs, integrated with MoonPay's Open Wallet Standard for cross-chain interoperability.
Canton Network is the only top-20 market cap blockchain ($5.7B) without dedicated embedded wallet tooling. Every competing L1 ecosystem has mature solutions: Privy (acquired by Stripe, 75M+ accounts) and Dynamic (acquired by Fireblocks for ~$90M, 50M+ wallets). This gap forces every Canton application builder to independently solve wallet integration, authentication, and key management from scratch — duplicating effort by 3–6 months per team, introducing security risks, and directly throttling ecosystem growth.
The complete SDK — authentication, wallet engine, Canton integration, UI components, and self-hostable backend services — is published under Apache 2.0. Any developer can run a fully functional wallet stack with zero commercial dependency. Any Canton application can integrate the SDK in under 30 minutes, directly accelerating ecosystem growth and developer adoption.
