#### 2.2 Authentication Module (`@keyvoy/auth`)

This module bridges familiar login methods to Canton wallet provisioning. It is the entry point for every end-user interaction.

**Social Login Providers**

The module implements the complete OAuth 2.0 / OIDC authentication flow for each provider — managing redirect URIs, token exchange, ID token validation (JWT signature, issuer, audience, expiry), and session creation.

| Provider | Protocol | Use Case | Key Implementation Detail |
|----------|----------|----------|--------------------------|
| Google | OAuth 2.0 + OIDC | Primary consumer login (90%+ coverage) | ID token validation via Google's JWKS endpoint, email_verified claim required |
| GitHub | OAuth 2.0 | Developer-focused apps, SDK docs portals | Scopes: read:user, user:email. Token exchange via server-side secret |
| Discord | OAuth 2.0 | DAO tooling, community governance | Scopes: identify, email. Guild membership for gated access |
| Email + Password | Custom | Traditional enterprise users | bcrypt hashing (cost=12), email verification magic links, rate limiting (5 attempts/15min) |
| Email Magic Links | Custom | Passwordless consumer login | Time-limited tokens (15min), single-use enforcement, configurable delivery (SendGrid/AWS SES/Resend) |
| SMS OTP | Custom | Phone-based verification | 6-digit codes, 5min expiry, carrier-agnostic (Twilio/AWS SNS), international formatting |

Additional providers (Apple Sign-In, Passkeys/WebAuthn) are planned for post-launch releases based on ecosystem demand.

**Institutional Authentication**

| Method | Standard | Target Users | Key Implementation Detail |
|--------|----------|-------------|--------------------------|
| OpenID Connect | OIDC 1.0 | Enterprise OIDC providers | Authorization code + PKCE, discovery document auto-config, custom claim mapping |
| SAML 2.0 SSO | SAML 2.0 | Banks, asset managers (Okta, Azure AD, OneLogin, PingIdentity) | SP-initiated + IdP-initiated flows, signed assertions, encrypted NameIDs, attribute mapping to Canton wallet properties |
| MFA (second factor) | TOTP | All institutional users, optional for consumer | TOTP (Google Authenticator, Authy), SMS OTP as second factor. Configurable per-organization enforcement |
| API Keys | Custom | Service-to-service backend integrations | Scoped permissions (read/write/admin), IP allowlisting, automatic rotation, per-organization isolation |

