## Motivation

### Why is this valuable to the Canton ecosystem?

**1. Canton is the only top-20 blockchain without wallet infrastructure.**

The Wallet-as-a-Service market reached $2 billion in 2025 (30% CAGR through 2033). Every major L1 has mature providers: Privy handles 75M+ accounts for Ethereum/Solana apps, Dynamic powers 50M+ wallets for Kraken and Magic Eden. Canton has zero. This absence is the single largest bottleneck for developer adoption.

**2. The acquisition wave proves wallet infra is existentially important.**

Stripe acquired Privy (75M+ accounts, $41.3M previously raised). Fireblocks paid ~$90M for Dynamic. These are confirmation that wallet infrastructure is the critical enabling layer for blockchain ecosystems. Stripe's CEO described wallets as "programmable vaults" essential for internet-native financial services. Canton needs its own wallet infrastructure or developers will build on chains that have it.

**3. Each wallet = network value creation.**

Every wallet provisioned through Keyvoy creates a Canton party that generates Ledger API activity. Every transaction generates CC fees that are burned through the Burn-Mint Equilibrium. More wallets → more transactions → more burn → healthier token economics.

**4. Institutional adoption requires enterprise-grade wallet UX.**

Canton's core users — banks, asset managers, fintechs — will not build applications that require end-users to manage seed phrases. Enterprise-grade embedded wallets with SSO, signing policies, and compliance tooling are table stakes. Keyvoy provides this as a shared resource.

**5. Developer retention depends on tooling.**

Canton must compete for developer mindshare against Ethereum, Solana, Base, and others that have mature wallet SDKs. By providing Privy/Dynamic-equivalent infrastructure, Canton signals to the global developer community that it takes developer experience seriously.

**6. AI agents are the next wave of Canton users — and they need wallets.**

Over 340,000 on-chain agent wallets existed in Q1 2026. Every major payment protocol (x402 by Coinbase, MPP by Stripe/Tempo) assumes agents already have a wallet. Canton has no agent wallet infrastructure.

Cayvox Labs has built Canton's agentic wallet layer: 178 tests, Canton 3.4.10 validated, published on crates.io. AI agents can create Canton wallets, sign DAML commands, and query contracts through MCP tools — with policy enforcement before any key material is touched. This is not a plan — it is shipped, tested, open-source infrastructure.

The layer is also integrated with MoonPay's Open Wallet Standard (backed by PayPal, Circle, Ethereum Foundation, and 15+ others), connecting Canton to the broader cross-chain agent economy.

